106
00:05:08,942 --> 00:05:12,071
Chrissy, our Airbnb
is five full blocks away,

107
00:05:12,145 --> 00:05:13,636
I am exhausted.

108
00:05:14,314 --> 00:05:18,979
And it's snowing cats,
dogs, and reindeer out there.

109
00:05:19,920 --> 00:05:22,185
It's good you got in from
Vermont when you did.

110
00:05:23,089 --> 00:05:24,148
See?

111
00:05:24,257 --> 00:05:27,284
No, sorry, I meant,
because we need to start

112
00:05:27,360 --> 00:05:29,829
Chrissy on an immune
checkpoint inhibitor tonight.

113
00:05:29,963 --> 00:05:33,525
It will make her glioblastoma
respond better to her clinical trial.

114
00:05:34,000 --> 00:05:36,697
That sounds like something I
should probably tell the kids.

115
00:05:38,338 --> 00:05:39,431
Tell them.

116
00:05:39,706 --> 00:05:42,107
You sound exactly
like me and my wife.

117
00:05:42,475 --> 00:05:44,671
Always arguing
about silly things.

118
00:05:45,178 --> 00:05:48,148
I'm going back to our Airbnb,
so I can get a few hours sleep.

119
00:05:48,315 --> 00:05:50,944
I will bring you your
phone in the morning.

120
00:05:53,653 --> 00:05:56,782
Shouldn't having cancer mean
that I get to win every argument?

121
00:06:03,363 --> 00:06:05,203
Hey, there's my deputy.
Wait, where's your hat?

122
00:06:05,465 --> 00:06:07,661
Oh, I forgot it
because, you know,

123
00:06:07,734 --> 00:06:09,278
I was forced out of the
warmth quite suddenly.

124
00:06:09,302 --> 00:06:12,670
Yeah, but not wearing a hat
in this weather is a little insane.

125
00:06:12,739 --> 00:06:14,717
Yeah, I'm your doctor, Max.
Not the other way around.

126
00:06:14,741 --> 00:06:15,800
Hey, are you okay?

127
00:06:15,876 --> 00:06:17,037
Um...

128
00:06:20,580 --> 00:06:21,809
I'm fine, I just...

129
00:06:23,750 --> 00:06:26,549
I just had to walk four
blocks in a blizzard because

130
00:06:26,653 --> 00:06:28,679
my cab couldn't get
past this big accident

131
00:06:28,755 --> 00:06:30,275
that's happened up
the street... Where?

132
00:06:30,357 --> 00:06:33,327
35th and 1st, but
there's no casualties,

133
00:06:33,393 --> 00:06:35,988
just people thought
they could drive in this.

134
00:06:36,429 --> 00:06:37,488
Wait, what is it?

135
00:06:37,564 --> 00:06:39,396
That's right in
front of Station 27.

136
00:06:41,701 --> 00:06:42,812
I was just coming to find you.

137
00:06:42,836 --> 00:06:44,347
When's the last time you
got an ambulance in here?

138
00:06:44,371 --> 00:06:45,566
Forty-seven minutes ago.

139
00:06:49,242 --> 00:06:50,767
This is Max Goodwin
at New Amsterdam.

140
00:06:50,877 --> 00:06:53,108
I need to talk to EMS
Division Chief Molinari.

141
00:06:53,246 --> 00:06:54,270
<i>I'm on.</i>

142
00:06:54,381 --> 00:06:55,421
What's going on out there?

143
00:06:55,515 --> 00:06:57,211
<i>There's a huge pileup on 35th.</i>

144
00:06:57,284 --> 00:07:00,083
<i>Snowplows can't get through
to Murray Hill or Kips Bay.</i>

145
00:07:00,186 --> 00:07:01,381
Are calls coming in?

146
00:07:01,454 --> 00:07:04,424
<i>Many, but without snowplows,
our vehicles can't get to them.</i>

147
00:07:07,260 --> 00:07:09,140
Chief, send me a log of
all your incoming calls,

148
00:07:09,195 --> 00:07:11,357
and keep them coming. <i>Copy that.</i>

149
00:07:11,431 --> 00:07:12,871
If people can't
get to this hospital,

150
00:07:12,933 --> 00:07:15,095
then we need to bring
this hospital to them.

151
00:07:22,442 --> 00:07:25,970
I know being stuck at the
hospital during a blizzard sucks,

152
00:07:26,079 --> 00:07:27,239
but do you know what's worse?

153
00:07:27,280 --> 00:07:31,081
Needing 911 in a blizzard and
being told that no one is coming.

154
00:07:31,151 --> 00:07:35,714
So I have here a list of 911 calls
within a half-mile of New Amsterdam.

155
00:07:35,789 --> 00:07:38,156
Ambulances can't get
to them, but we can.

156
00:07:38,258 --> 00:07:41,387
And, yes, conditions are bad
out there, but we have got parkas,

157
00:07:41,461 --> 00:07:45,091
and we have got emergency
packs, and we have got chutzpah.

158
00:07:45,265 --> 00:07:47,757
Everybody is gonna
pair up for safety

159
00:07:47,834 --> 00:07:50,668
and we're gonna give you a
GPS Locator, so we can track you

160
00:07:50,770 --> 00:07:52,295
from right here in the hospital.

161
00:07:52,405 --> 00:07:54,670
And to be clear,
nobody has to go.

162
00:07:54,808 --> 00:07:56,470
But we're their only shot, so...

163
00:07:57,510 --> 00:07:58,569
Any volunteers?

164
00:08:03,650 --> 00:08:05,915
Sweet. I've missed
field medicine.

165
00:08:05,986 --> 00:08:07,010
I'll go with you.

166
00:08:07,120 --> 00:08:08,247
Casey and Flores, yes.

167
00:08:08,321 --> 00:08:11,780
You guys have a doorman who's
arm was sliced by a snow blower.

168
00:08:11,858 --> 00:08:13,850
1891 East 23rd street.

169
00:08:15,095 --> 00:08:17,273
Nottingham, Moreland, you've
got a college kid who OD'd.

170
00:08:17,297 --> 00:08:18,765
32nd and 1st.

171
00:08:18,832 --> 00:08:20,109
Let's make sure
we have naloxone.

172
00:08:20,133 --> 00:08:22,078
Great, Levy Park we have
a man who has fallen down,

173
00:08:22,102 --> 00:08:23,342
can't move, may be unconscious.

174
00:08:23,436 --> 00:08:24,460
On it. Thank you.

175
00:08:24,537 --> 00:08:25,596
I'll go with you.

176
00:08:25,672 --> 00:08:28,836
And calls keep pouring
in so just find your patient,

177
00:08:28,942 --> 00:08:30,419
treat them, and get back
here so we can send you

178
00:08:30,443 --> 00:08:31,854
right back out to
treat the next person.

179
00:08:31,878 --> 00:08:34,541
And, guys, let's
be careful out there.

180
00:08:36,049 --> 00:08:37,779
Always wanted to say that.

181
00:08:41,988 --> 00:08:43,616
- Hi, everybody.
- I'm here.

182
00:08:44,557 --> 00:08:47,527
Okay, hey, raise your hand if
you find the storm scary right now.

183
00:08:47,627 --> 00:08:49,357
Big kids, I know it's
not cool to be scared,

184
00:08:49,462 --> 00:08:51,374
but I bet the younger kids
will feel a lot better knowing

185
00:08:51,398 --> 00:08:53,042
they're not the only ones
who are spooked right now.

186
00:08:53,066 --> 00:08:54,364
So, hands up. I got mine up.

187
00:08:54,501 --> 00:08:55,525
I'm scared.

188
00:08:55,802 --> 00:08:57,327
But guess what, guys.
I have good news.

189
00:08:57,470 --> 00:08:59,530
We got games. We
got games galore.

190
00:08:59,639 --> 00:09:01,801
We got hot cocoa
and we got Gladys.

191
00:09:01,908 --> 00:09:03,519
How bad could it be if
we got Gladys, right?

192
00:09:03,543 --> 00:09:04,703
Everyone, follow me. Come on.

193
00:09:04,744 --> 00:09:06,542
I'm gonna take you
into the fun room.

194
00:09:06,646 --> 00:09:07,807
Yeah. Yeah, yeah, yeah.

195
00:09:07,881 --> 00:09:09,543
And even though
it's scary out there...

196
