Avi, that's not helpful.

197
00:09:13,420 --> 00:09:15,821
No, actually, it is
kind of helpful, Avi.

198
00:09:15,889 --> 00:09:17,915
Thank you. Because
that freaked me out.

199
00:09:18,024 --> 00:09:19,502
Right? My heart
jumped out of my chest.

200
00:09:19,526 --> 00:09:21,324
But now that I
know it was just Avi,

201
00:09:21,394 --> 00:09:23,420
I don't have to be
scared anymore. Right?

202
00:09:23,530 --> 00:09:24,707
Because the more
you understand things,

203
00:09:24,731 --> 00:09:25,994
the less scary they are.

204
00:09:26,199 --> 00:09:28,930
Which brings me to
the star of this evening,

205
00:09:29,035 --> 00:09:31,266
the world's most comprehensive
and cool weather app.

206
00:09:31,371 --> 00:09:32,395
Look at this thing.

207
00:09:32,505 --> 00:09:35,305
We're gonna learn all about the
storm through the majesty of satellite.

208
00:09:36,242 --> 00:09:38,177
Oh... Skimbleshanks.

209
00:09:38,778 --> 00:09:40,440
My anemometer
is not transmitting.

210
00:09:40,880 --> 00:09:41,904
Okay. Uh...

211
00:09:43,016 --> 00:09:44,917
Okay. Listen, Gladys,
why don't you go in there,

212
00:09:45,051 --> 00:09:46,178
break out <i>le</i> cocoa.

213
00:09:46,252 --> 00:09:48,244
Everybody, make me a mug, okay?

214
00:09:48,354 --> 00:09:51,415
Extra marshmallows for me
and I will be right back, I promise.

215
00:09:51,791 --> 00:09:52,850
I'll be right back.

216
00:09:55,962 --> 00:09:57,453
Candelario, what you got?

217
00:09:58,898 --> 00:10:00,127
EMS just got a call.

218
00:10:00,233 --> 00:10:02,745
A man on East 21st Street heard
a crash in the adjacent apartment.

219
00:10:02,769 --> 00:10:04,237
Older woman lives there alone.

220
00:10:04,304 --> 00:10:05,636
He's been knocking,
but no answer.

221
00:10:05,738 --> 00:10:06,849
No, no, I'll go. No,
I think I should go.

222
00:10:06,873 --> 00:10:08,250
No, stay here, track
everyone in the field,

223
00:10:08,274 --> 00:10:09,902
