00:11:38,131 --> 00:11:39,497
So I can keep track of you.

250
00:11:54,147 --> 00:11:55,467
Mrs. Gallagher?

251
00:11:56,149 --> 00:11:57,640
There she is.

252
00:11:59,886 --> 00:12:01,320
I can't feel a pulse. I got you.

253
00:12:02,655 --> 00:12:03,679
Starting compressions.

254
00:12:04,891 --> 00:12:05,915
Clear.

255
00:12:08,595 --> 00:12:12,191
I don't feel a pulse.
Going again. Clear.

256
00:12:15,168 --> 00:12:17,433
I got a pulse. She's back.

257
00:12:23,409 --> 00:12:24,707
Have you seen our guy?

258
00:12:26,679 --> 00:12:28,170
I can barely see you.

259
00:12:30,016 --> 00:12:31,541
What's that?

260
00:12:33,086 --> 00:12:35,214
Oh, God. That's him!

261
00:12:42,629 --> 00:12:43,927
Sir, can you hear me?

262
00:12:47,133 --> 00:12:49,068
Equal round, reactive to light.

263
00:12:49,135 --> 00:12:52,196
His heart rate's around 30. Cold
weather really slowed him down.

264
00:12:52,272 --> 00:12:53,763
I can't move. It's okay.

265
00:12:53,873 --> 00:12:55,398
You fell and hit your head.

266
00:12:55,475 --> 00:12:58,775
- What's your name?
- Hugh Torone.

267
00:12:58,878 --> 00:13:01,074
I'm Dr. Reynolds,
this is Dr. Jessup.

268
00:13:01,147 --> 00:13:03,742
We're from New Amsterdam.
We're here to help you.

269
00:13:03,816 --> 00:13:05,444
Go help my husband.

270
00:13:06,319 --> 00:13:07,548
Your husband?

271
00:13:07,620 --> 00:13:11,148
I was running home from the
pharmacy when I slipped and fell.

272
00:13:12,659 --> 00:13:18,155
His glucose was
monitoring 475 when I left.

273
00:13:20,166 --> 00:13:21,657
Mr. Torone, where do you live?

274
00:13:21,768 --> 00:13:28,072
Just a few blocks from here
on 29th, 464. Apartment 1043.

275
00:13:28,675 --> 00:13:32,112
Okay, and the prescription?
It's in my left pocket.

276
00:13:32,178 --> 00:13:33,771
Got it.

277
00:13:34,514 --> 00:13:35,573
Run!

278
00:13:35,648 --> 00:13:39,949
29th, 464. Apartment 1043.

279
00:13:40,019 --> 00:13:42,454
Okay. Don't worry,
I got you, all right?

280
00:13:42,522 --> 00:13:43,581
You're gonna be all right.

281
00:14:05,144 --> 00:14:07,010
Jessup!

282
00:14:08,548 --> 00:14:10,540
Jessup!

283
00:14:17,557 --> 00:14:19,651
You really shouldn't
have come all this way.

284
00:14:19,726 --> 00:14:23,493
Unfortunately, Marlene, no ambulances
can get through the snow right now.

285
00:14:23,563 --> 00:14:25,532
Please, don't waste
your time with me.

286
00:14:26,165 --> 00:14:28,177
Her blood pressure is dropping.
We're gonna need Levophed.

287
00:14:28,201 --> 00:14:30,136
That's back at
the hospital. Yeah.

288
00:14:34,407 --> 00:14:35,568
I'll go.

289
00:14:36,342 --> 00:14:37,810
No, I will. No, I got it.

290
00:14:37,877 --> 00:14:38,970
I'll be really fast.

291
00:14:39,045 --> 00:14:41,357
You're not supposed to be fast,
you're supposed to be taking it slowly!

292
00:14:41,381 --> 00:14:43,381
I came to keep an eye
on you, but it doesn't matter

293
00:14:43,483 --> 00:14:46,146
because the only doctor
you ever listen to is yourself.

294
00:14:48,154 --> 00:14:51,090
I am going to the hospital, you
are staying here, end of story.

295
00:14:51,190 --> 00:14:52,317
Excuse me, please.

296
00:14:52,825 --> 00:14:54,259
Ugh!

297
00:14:56,095 --> 00:14:57,529
Okay.

298
00:14:58,898 --> 00:15:02,699
She's very good
at what she does.

299
00:15:02,769 --> 00:15:07,332
She's... Dr. Sharpe
will be right back.

300
00:15:07,407 --> 00:15:09,740
Thank you, but it
really doesn't matter.

301
00:15:11,377 --> 00:15:12,675
You're gonna be fine.

302
00:15:12,745 --> 00:15:15,271
No, I won't. I'm a clairvoyant.

303
00:15:15,381 --> 00:15:17,077
I've seen the future.

304
00:15:17,183 --> 00:15:19,675
Today's the day
I'm going to die.

305
00:15:24,424 --> 00:15:25,448
Whoa!

306
00:15:32,932 --> 00:15:34,059
Oh!

307
00:15:45,645 --> 00:15:48,581
All right, come
on. I can do this.

308
00:15:48,648 --> 00:15:52,710
Wisconsin Strong. Let's
go, Iggy. There you go.

309
00:16:00,460 --> 00:16:02,292
Oh, God! Jesus!

310
00:16:02,395 --> 00:16:04,887
Oh, God, no!

311
00:16:24,984 --> 00:16:27,510
Hey! Hello?

312
00:16:34,126 --> 00:16:37,153
Heart rate's down to 48
and weak. I can barely feel it.

313
00:16:37,263 --> 00:16:38,925
She stopped
breathing on her own.

314
00:16:40,132 --> 00:16:41,760
O-2 sat down to 89%.

315
00:16:41,834 --> 00:16:43,325
Grab the Ambu bag.

316
00:16:50,543 --> 00:16:52,011
O-2 sats still in the 80s.

317
00:16:52,111 --> 00:16:53,989
I'm gonna tilt her head
back to get a better seal.

318
00:16:54,013 --> 00:16:55,253
She's going to aspirate.

319
00:16:57,984 --> 00:16:59,043
Move.

320
00:16:59,685 --> 00:17:00,812
Turn her on her side.

321
00:17:02,154 --> 00:17:03,274
Keep working the bag.

322
00:17:03,322 --> 00:17:07,453
One, two, three.

323
00:17:11,364 --> 00:17:12,457
Okay.

324
00:17:21,674 --> 00:17:23,370
Just give it a minute.

325
00:17:33,853 --> 00:17:36,823
Get a message to Dr. Thomas.
She's gonna need to bring charcoal.

326
00:17:36,889 --> 00:17:38,881
Got it. Thank you, Lauren.

327
00:17:55,374 --> 00:17:56,774
Mr. Torone,

328
00:17:56,876 --> 00:17:59,368
you need to stay
absolutely still.

329
00:17:59,445 --> 00:18:01,778
Can't you just
pull me off of it?

330
00:18:01,881 --> 00:18:04,942
No, not without risking
injury to other organs.

331
00:18:05,051 --> 00:18:06,917
I gotta find a way to
get you to the hospital

332
00:18:07,019 --> 00:18:08,954
without removing
you from the spike.

333
00:18:09,055 --> 00:18:10,921
How do you know
it didn't hit my heart?

334
00:18:11,424 --> 00:18:14,053
Because we wouldn't be having
this conversation, Mr. Torone.

335
00:18:14,126 --> 00:18:17,290
Feels like you're about to become
an important person in my life.

336
00:18:17,396 --> 00:18:19,365
Just call me Hugh.

337
00:18:19,966 --> 00:18:21,025
All right, Hugh.

338
00:18:21,100 --> 00:18:22,432
Right now I'm just trying to

339
00:18:22,535 --> 00:18:24,613
figure out exactly how
this spike is penetrating you.

340
00:18:24,637 --> 00:18:26,868
Well, it definitely doesn't
feel like missionary.

341
00:18:28,307 --> 00:18:30,867
Oh, God. Apologies.

342
00:18:30,943 --> 00:18:32,775
Eric says I should
know people a little better

343
00:18:32,878 --> 00:18:34,642
before I make
those kinds of jokes.

344
00:18:36,549 --> 00:18:38,040
Lift up a little.

345
00:18:38,484 --> 00:18:40,715
Oh, God. Thank you.

346
00:18:40,786 --> 00:18:42,482
I'm not cold.

347
00:18:44,790 --> 00:18:45,985
You're not?

348
00:19:01,307 --> 00:19:02,400
Hey.

349
00:19:02,475 --> 00:19:04,808
You were asleep. You feel okay?

350
00:19:05,077 --> 00:19:06,306
Oh.

351
00:19:06,679 --> 00:19:08,807
I thought maybe I was dead.

352
00:19:08,914 --> 00:19:12,009
No, Marlene. You are
not gonna die today.

353
00:19:12,118 --> 00:19:13,848
Not on my watch.
Let's sit you up.

354
00:19:13,953 --> 00:19:15,649
What do you know?

355
00:19:15,755 --> 00:19:19,089
You're a doctor, you
believe in science.

356
00:19:19,158 --> 00:19:21,650
Facts. The known.

357
00:19:21,761 --> 00:19:25,129
Well, yeah. Me and
most other people.

358
00:19:25,665 --> 00:19:27,031
I believe in the hidden.

359
00:19:28,000 --> 00:19:29,195
I believe there's

360
00:19:29,301 --> 00:19:33,170
a deeper spiritual reality that
extends beyond pure reason.

361
00:19:33,272 --> 00:19:36,106
And while that's fascinating,
it doesn't have to kill you.

362
00:19:39,178 --> 00:19:42,205
Why don't we ask the cards?

363
00:19:42,314 --> 00:19:43,839
Split the deck.

364
00:19:43,949 --> 00:19:47,511
And show me the top
card of the bottom half.

365
00:19:49,321 --> 00:19:50,482
Uh...

366
00:19:51,490 --> 00:19:52,549
Yeah, okay. Okay.

367
00:19:56,729 --> 00:19:59,130
Ask the cards.

368
00:19:59,198 --> 00:20:01,064
Here we go, split these.

369
00:20:03,502 --> 00:20:05,664
What do you... What do you see?

370
00:20:05,738 --> 00:20:07,639
King of swords. Mmm.

371
00:20:09,875 --> 00:20:10,899
Reversed.

372
00:20:12,211 --> 00:20:16,342
A very powerful card.
But one to be wary of.

373
00:20:19,018 --> 00:20:23,251
Hmm. You help people,
sometimes at a detriment to yourself.

374
00:20:25,224 --> 00:20:27,386
Yes, because I'm a doctor.

375
00:20:29,428 --> 00:20:30,987
I see a woman.

376
00:20:33,199 --> 00:20:35,725
But there have been
some bumps recently.

377
00:20:40,673 --> 00:20:45,611
Okay. It's true, but
that's every marriage.

378
00:20:46,378 --> 00:20:49,371
You try to meet her needs,

379
00:20:49,882 --> 00:20:53,284
but sometimes
it's just not enough.

380
00:20:55,421 --> 00:20:57,117
You're going to lose her.

381
00:20:57,223 --> 00:20:58,555
Yeah, okay.

382
00:20:59,391 --> 00:21:02,555
Why don't you try to
get some rest, Marlene.

383
00:21:09,401 --> 00:21:11,267
Look,

384
00:21:11,370 --> 00:21:16,240
my wife and I have been
through a lot this year,

385
00:21:16,308 --> 00:21:18,072
but we are good now,

386
00:21:18,144 --> 00:21:21,774
so I'm not gonna lose her.

387
00:21:22,114 --> 00:21:24,106
I'm not talking about your wife.

388
00:21:25,117 --> 00:21:27,052
You and your wife are fine.

389
00:21:28,120 --> 00:21:30,112
There's someone else.

390
00:21:33,425 --> 00:21:36,953
Someone you care for, deeply.

391
00:21:38,964 --> 00:21:41,763
And you are going to lose her.

392
00:22:18,938 --> 00:22:20,372
Hang in there, Hugh.

393
00:22:21,607 --> 00:22:23,269
How you holding up?

394
00:22:23,342 --> 00:22:25,334
You know, stabbed.

395
00:22:27,947 --> 00:22:28,971
Ah! Found it!

396
00:22:32,885 --> 00:22:34,945
There's a screw
attached to the spike.

397
00:22:35,020 --> 00:22:38,013
If I could just loosen
it, I could remove you

398
00:22:38,123 --> 00:22:39,386
and the spike together.

399
00:22:40,192 --> 00:22:41,820
Oh, like a couple.

400
00:22:42,361 --> 00:22:45,490
Sorry. Even with painkillers
you're gonna feel some stuff.

401
00:22:47,399 --> 00:22:49,163
Stop!

402
00:22:51,971 --> 00:22:54,031
Nope.

403
00:22:54,139 --> 00:22:56,631
No, no. I'm sorry.
Keep going, keep going.

404
00:22:57,810 --> 00:22:59,870
Why don't you
tell me about Eric?

405
00:22:59,979 --> 00:23:01,470
What's he like?

406
00:23:02,581 --> 00:23:04,573
We've been
married for six years.

407
00:23:05,751 --> 00:23:08,653
Together since 1987.

408
00:23:09,855 --> 00:23:14,020
Eric is smart and funny.

409
00:23:14,727 --> 00:23:16,355
Oh, yeah?

410
00:23:18,998 --> 00:23:20,398
So loving.

411
00:23:21,533 --> 00:23:24,560
He's also the world's
best procrastinator.

412
00:23:24,670 --> 00:23:29,335
He promised he would
refill his insulin two days ago.

413
00:23:30,776 --> 00:23:32,870
I should have
just done it for him.

414
00:23:32,945 --> 00:23:35,437
Yeah, look where
that literally landed me.

415
00:23:37,583 --> 00:23:40,018
Yeah, my mom
forgets to do things.

416
00:23:40,085 --> 00:23:42,179
Simple things, you know?

417
00:23:42,254 --> 00:23:47,591
Like I told her, before the storm
hit, to go to my sister's and she forgot.

418
00:23:48,794 --> 00:23:52,196
But she's old, you
know. It's not her fault.

419
00:23:52,264 --> 00:23:54,790
I still get mad at her.

420
00:23:54,900 --> 00:23:56,459
I don't even know why.

421
00:23:57,403 --> 00:23:59,963
Maybe you're scared

422
00:24:00,072 --> 00:24:03,270
that she's starting to decline.

423
00:24:07,446 --> 00:24:10,075
I don't know, I never really
talked to anyone about it.

424
00:24:13,585 --> 00:24:14,814
No!

425
00:24:16,655 --> 00:24:18,317
Damn thing broke.

426
00:24:23,562 --> 00:24:25,622
You have to leave
me now, don't you?

427
00:24:29,668 --> 00:24:30,727
No.

428
00:24:31,437 --> 00:24:32,905
You're coming with me.

429
00:24:35,274 --> 00:24:38,472
I thought that wasn't an option.

430
00:24:38,577 --> 00:24:40,307
Well, now it's our only option.

431
00:24:40,980 --> 00:24:44,508
If you pull me off, won't I die?

432
00:24:46,185 --> 00:24:49,917
If we stay here,
you definitely will.

433
00:24:54,493 --> 00:24:55,688
Hey!

434
00:24:56,495 --> 00:24:57,656
Hey!

435
00:25:01,166 --> 00:25:04,159
Hello! Hello!

436
00:25:05,037 --> 00:25:07,472
I fully recognize that
I'm probably yelling

437
00:25:07,539 --> 00:25:08,871
at nobody right now,

438
00:25:08,974 --> 00:25:10,806
but if you can hear
me, I'm up on the roof

439
00:25:10,876 --> 00:25:12,811
and I would rather
not die of exposure.

440
00:25:12,878 --> 00:25:14,437
Thank you!

441
00:25:16,048 --> 00:25:17,107
Whoa! Hey, hey.

442
00:25:17,182 --> 00:25:19,617
Don't let that door shut.
Don't let the door shut!

443
00:25:19,685 --> 00:25:21,051
Damn it.

444
00:25:24,823 --> 00:25:25,847
Avi?

445
00:25:27,326 --> 00:25:28,385
Avi!

446
00:25:29,495 --> 00:25:30,554
Avi!

447
00:25:31,463 --> 00:25:33,295
Hey, Avi!

448
00:25:34,366 --> 00:25:35,390
Avi!

449
00:25:42,307 --> 00:25:45,175
Okay, Marlene, this should
be making you feel better.

450
00:25:45,411 --> 00:25:47,073
It doesn't,

451
00:25:47,179 --> 00:25:49,148
but that's because
I'm gonna be dead.

452
00:25:49,214 --> 00:25:51,240
Marlene, what did
we say about that?

453
00:25:51,417 --> 00:25:54,410
Hey, can I...

454
00:25:54,520 --> 00:25:57,012
Can I talk to you
for a second? Sure.

455
00:25:59,691 --> 00:26:01,592
Look, I know that
we can't leave her,

456
00:26:01,693 --> 00:26:03,671
but Candelario really
needs us back at the hospital.

457
00:26:03,695 --> 00:26:05,755
Hang on.

458
00:26:11,937 --> 00:26:14,532
I know that I haven't
always been...

459
00:26:20,612 --> 00:26:22,581
You've been so...

460
00:26:23,415 --> 00:26:25,543
You've always...

461
00:26:30,122 --> 00:26:31,920
Never mind. I forgot.

462
00:26:32,624 --> 00:26:33,768
Yeah, it's fine.
Don't worry about it.

463
00:26:33,792 --> 00:26:36,125
Yeah, no, sorry.
I forgot. It's just,

464
00:26:36,228 --> 00:26:39,062
chemo brain strikes
again, so, yeah.

465
00:26:39,131 --> 00:26:41,123
I know that we need to
get back to the hospital,

466
00:26:41,233 --> 00:26:43,464
but we really need
to monitor Marlene.

467
00:26:43,802 --> 00:26:45,270
Mmm. Um...

468
00:26:45,370 --> 00:26:47,601
Yeah. Telemetry.

469
00:26:47,706 --> 00:26:48,969
We could get the equipment

470
00:26:49,074 --> 00:26:51,771
from New Amsterdam
and monitor her from here.

471
00:26:52,444 --> 00:26:55,539
Telemetry. Helen,
you are the best.

472
00:26:57,049 --> 00:27:02,249
I think that's kinda what
I was trying to tell you.

473
00:27:04,890 --> 00:27:05,914
Um...

474
00:27:06,558 --> 00:27:08,720
Marlene, Dr. Sharpe
has saved the day.

475
00:27:08,794 --> 00:27:10,939
We are going to monitor you
remotely from New Amsterdam.

476
00:27:10,963 --> 00:27:13,831
I will be right
back. No, no, no.

477
00:27:13,932 --> 00:27:15,628
No, you look wiped
out from your last trip.

478
00:27:15,734 --> 00:27:17,445
You stay, I'm gonna get
the equipment this time,

479
00:27:17,469 --> 00:27:18,903
but I am gonna go slow,

480
00:27:19,738 --> 00:27:21,798
and I will take care of myself.

481
00:27:21,907 --> 00:27:24,274
Because I love my doctor.

482
00:27:37,256 --> 00:27:41,125
Have the two of you been
working together for a long time?

483
00:27:43,028 --> 00:27:44,997
No. Why?

484
00:27:45,831 --> 00:27:48,665
I just sense a very strong vibe.

485
00:27:54,673 --> 00:27:56,539
Okay.

486
00:28:00,812 --> 00:28:02,940
Honey, I'm sorry,

487
00:28:03,015 --> 00:28:06,315
but it's never gonna work
out between you and Max.

488
00:28:17,863 --> 00:28:22,665
I don't need it to work
out between me and Max.

489
00:28:22,734 --> 00:28:26,398
Max is married, I
have a boyfriend.

490
00:28:26,505 --> 00:28:28,906
And most importantly,
I am his doctor.

491
00:28:38,350 --> 00:28:40,080
How you doing, Avi?

492
00:28:41,987 --> 00:28:44,547
I don't want to talk about it.

493
00:28:47,659 --> 00:28:49,651
Storms, man.

494
00:28:49,728 --> 00:28:51,822
It's just pressure
and precipitation,

495
00:28:51,897 --> 00:28:53,697
but, man, they make
us feel stuff, don't they?

496
00:28:55,000 --> 00:28:56,730
Riddled with the
feels right now.

497
00:28:58,070 --> 00:28:59,936
What about you?

498
00:29:00,038 --> 00:29:01,238
How's the storm make you feel?

499
00:29:04,176 --> 00:29:05,200
I don't know.

500
00:29:05,277 --> 00:29:06,336
Yeah, you do.

